<item>
            <title>[SPR-512] SimpleMappingExceptionResolver not iterating Exception Mappings in user-determined order</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-512</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In class SimpleMappingExceptionResolver, the Exception mappings are iterated in a random order, so that if the user maps first sub-classes and then superclasses, the superclass may be hit first.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;property name=&quot;exceptionMappings&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;props&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;prop key=&quot;com.blah.MyException&quot;&amp;gt;oops&amp;lt;/prop&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;prop key=&quot;java.lang.Exception&quot;&amp;gt;error&amp;lt;/prop&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/props&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
If com.blah.MyException is thrown, java.lang.Exception is hit before com.blah.MyException, so that the view &quot;error&quot; is returned instead of &quot;oops&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probable fix:&lt;br/&gt;
this.exceptionMappings = new HashMap(mappings.size());&lt;br/&gt;
Should be:&lt;br/&gt;
this.exceptionMappings = new LinkedHashMap(mappings.size());&lt;/p&gt;</description>
