                            <comment id="11676" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 4 Dec 2004 03:08:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point - thanks for the suggestion! However, I&apos;ve already changed the exception mapping completely, also solving this issue: Like rollback rules in transaction demarcation, SimpleMappingExceptionResolver accepts any exception class name patterns now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a concrete exception, the closest match will be found: that is, where the pattern matches the exception class name or the name of one of its superclasses with the least depth. So for a javax.servlet.ServletException, a mapping for &quot;ServletException&quot; will always be preferred, even if a mapping for &quot;java.lang.Exception&quot; comes first in the config file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
